-- Wake Forest Upsets Second-Ranked Miami in College Basketball
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-02-24T05:00:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-23/wake-forest-upsets-second-ranked-miami-in-college-basketball.html
Wake Forest University  defeated the
University of Miami 80-65, ending the second-ranked Hurricanes’
14-game winning streak.  C.J. Harris scored 23 points, making all five of his 3-
point shots, and Codi Miller-McIntyre added 15 points to lead
Wake (12-14, 5-9 Atlantic Coast Conference) to the home win
yesterday in Winston-Salem,  North Carolina .  Durand Scott scored 17 points for Miami (22-4, 13-1 ACC),
the last school in any of college basketball’s top six
conferences to get its first league loss.  In other games involving top-five teams, No. 3 Gonzaga
defeated San Diego 81-50 and No. 5 Florida topped Arkansas 71-
54.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
